This past Saturday I stopped in to order something. I hadn’t been to a McDonald’s in 2 years so I was craving their fries and decided to stop in to this nice looking location. I actually regretted going in after this experience. The cashier told me that I had to wait 2 minutes for the fries which is fine. I saw they had breakfast options in the afternoon so I decided to buy something. I told her I wanted 2 egg and cheese McMuffins with no meat. The fries were up and they left them there while my sandwiches were being made. While the two employees in the front were talking, my sandwiches were still not out. Minutes passed by and no sign of the sandwiches. After a while they handed me the fries and sandwiches but the lady then took the sandwiches and said they had sausage. So I had to wait even longer for them. Customers came in and their orders were taken. A few minutes after, they received their food and I was still waiting for mine. At this point I had had enough and I was going to ask for a refund. A few minutes after, I received my sandwiches. Went back to my seat to only find out that these sandwiches now had ham in them. I’ve never had an experience like this. I went back to the lady and the first thing she said was, “what now?” Totally rude. I’m not the person to be rude and talk to anyone with an attitude so I don’t understand why she gave me any. I thought I had clearly pointed out that I wanted egg and cheese with no meat. But I guess I wasn’t clear enough. So after I had eaten my fries, I still had to wait for my sandwiches. It took so long after to get my sandwiches. When I got them my appetite was gone so I left the location. This has been the worst experience I’ve ever had from a restaurant.
